#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:150
msgid "How it works"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:152
msgid "An eligible buyer opens their order and clicks the statutory withdrawal button (its wording is fixed by law for each language)."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:153
msgid "A two-step form appears: they review what they are withdrawing from, then explicitly confirm. No dark patterns, no extra hurdles."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:154
msgid "On confirmation the order is flagged \"withdrawal requested\", and the consumer immediately receives an acknowledgement of receipt by email (the legal durable medium) — plus a PDF and a permanent verifiable link when available."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:155
msgid "Every step is written to a tamper-evident, append-only log so you can prove what happened and when. You then handle the refund as usual."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:159
msgid "Where the button appears"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:161
msgid "In the customer account, on each eligible order (order list + order detail) and in the \"Right of withdrawal\" account tab."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:162
msgid "As a link inside the WooCommerce order emails, so guests without an account can reach it."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:163
msgid "Anywhere you place a shortcode: %s."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:167
msgid "Why the button might not show on an order"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:168
msgid "The button only appears where a real withdrawal right exists. It is hidden when:"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:173
msgid "The consumer is <strong>outside the scope of your applicability mode</strong> (currently: <strong>%s</strong>). For example, a Switzerland order is hidden in \"EU/EEA only\" mode — that is correct, Swiss law mandates no button."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:177
msgid "The order is not in a contract state (failed, cancelled, refunded, awaiting payment)."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:178
msgid "Every item is exempt under Art. 59 — either an <strong>unconditional</strong> reason (custom-made, perishable, dated services…), or one of the two <strong>conditional</strong> reasons (digital immediate access / service fully performed) <em>for which the consumer's consent was captured at checkout</em>. Note: <strong>physical products are never auto-hidden</strong> (they always keep the right), and a conditional item <strong>without</strong> captured consent also keeps the button — fail-safe toward the consumer."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/DashboardPage.php:179
msgid "It is a business (VAT) order, if you treat B2B as out of scope."
